 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugoanad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goanad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/01 11:35:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We're in Mr. Melee's World Now</span><hr size=1> Congrats COV!!!!<br>
<br>
That post was a gem! I loved all the references to movies\films\acting etc. Very demonstrative of attitudes that you encounter. Your post also irons out the problem nicely and places it within a readable format!<br>
<br>
I once posted an idea for a type of spell that would work in a group setting only and would kind of meaningfully integrate us into the mechanics that you describe. The post, and the idea, like so many ideas involving new spells ideas, barely got a read from most. Most likely because they know that new ideas aren't the stuff that Verant staff meetings are made of. So why read about and discuss new ideas when they'll never see the light of day?  I see their point.<br>
<br>
Once again..great post.<br>
<br>
Goanad <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujazyavechette.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JazyaVechette</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/01 3:05:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We're in Mr. Melee's World Now</span><hr size=1> One thing I can say about wizards. Most of the time they seem to be much more educated and aware players than the majority of the casters I group with. Enchanters are an exception. Mages, Druids, Necros, all have their stories. Clerics just want to watch those 6 red bars and not be bothered. Shamans, well, no real complaints about them...<br>
<br>
I cant speak for most players, but when there is a Wiz in my group in guk, I know a Wiz is doing their job when the mana checks go out. I know that whatever they dont have remaining in mana went directly into the HP of what we were fighting. To me, thats good use of mana.<br>
<br>
What I cant speak for? Those 14 icons that I got from the druid/shaman/cleric that sit up on my screen and supposedly make me better. HP and AC is nice for a tank, but why does your Rogue always need to be at +1200HP +40agi +60dex +50cha(cha?) when she hasnt got hit for the last 2 hours? Spend that mana healing the tank so our pulls can come in faster please. Thanks =)<br>
<br>
With a Wizard, I KNOW their mana went into the mob. When I'm not having to run around like an idiot chasing the mob who runs after the wiz who dropped 7dd's into it and opened the book, I know they know what they are doing.<br>
<br>
When a mob goes aggro on the cleric, the Wiz is the first one to root it off. When 'inc' is followed by 25 frogs running in the room, the Wizard is the one who has already started their evac. Who do I want behind me dropping spells into Nagafen? You guessed it.<br>
<br>
Ms. Melee <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucovenantu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Covenant U</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 7:33:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We're in Mr. Melee's World Now</span><hr size=1> Well your post is why I never try to speak in absolutes <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Much appreciated to hear of our worth from the guys and gals up front doing the heavy lifting.  I know I try to be very vocal in showing appreciation for a good puller melee, saying so often.  <br>
<br>
It's nice to hear it back sometimes, but it's rare.  This gets back to my problem with battle spam, it's obvious to see what a melee is doing, becuase we see you and the MOB and the spam tells us (unless we've turned it off) of your effectiveness.  <br>
<br>
I think some melee don't make the connection that those big bubbles of HP coming off the MOB isn't built up and lagging melee damage reporting, but our nukes <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   They also don't know who is rooting and stunning, even if I'm in a group with a cleric and a druid I usually insist on being main stunner/rooter.  1) they have better things to do, like heal! and 2) I have 3 stuns (soon 4 woot!) and solid roots, so I consider that to be my job.  <br>
<br>
Thanks again.  Nice to know the appreciation can be a two way  street.<br>
<br>
